<br>
Legionnaire Scale armor drops in Hate from the mummies, or at least it did before the Hate revamp. It's nice. I'm still wearing a few pieces at 58.<br>
<br>
The Iksar warrior weapon quest, sadly, has never been fully implemented. It stops at the 12/40 mancatcher (which is still sitting in my bank in the hopes I'll one day get to finish it).<br>
<br>
And ignore the guy who told you to quit. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I managed to survive just fine, untwinked, and even soloing a lot (gasp) when I couldn't find groups, up into my low 50s. The regen makes it possible. After that grouping became more compulsory. And I barely even notice the plate armor restriction, since Velious armors can be worn by Iksar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rithnok>Rithnok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.concordatangelis.org/forum/images/avatars/8eb114e73e2375844d3ba.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/12/03 4:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=820.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Iksar Warrior Quest</span><hr size=1> I got this one. *smiles* Speaking from 3 years experience playing the Iksar Samurai (Warrior) I will tell you that it's not that bad. And I play on the test server, I didn't 90% of my leveling soloing and those who do not believe it. Understand this, A warrior is only as good as his equipment and his ability to use it.<br>
<br>
In the low to mid levels this is how I did it.<br>
<br>
I started with blacksmithing used 25 points to put it up to basic top level and then I said to heck with all this other stuff and started making banded mail armor. I Then upgraded at about 110 skill in BS to Cab Scale armor, I NEVER went to Trooper Scale armor because it took up too much of my time and I wasn't skilled enough to get it. It's a little easier now to get Iksar blood so if you can Go to Imbued Cabilis Scale mail Armour.<br>
<br>
From this point you'll be about 30 - 35th level and I suggest from here, Worry more about your weapons than your armor because you will have the automatic Iksar AC bonus which is in and around 10 - 45% Depending on the piece of armor. This is also why Iksar have a 20% exp hit. So I just want to say keep at it... I've never had as much fun as I have had playing my Iksar Warrior<br>
